## 3. Surreal numbers—games become numbers

**Opening: Conway's universe**

In the 1970s, John Conway asked: what if we define a *number* to be any game position? Start with the empty game (no moves for Left or Right)—call it *0*. Define recursion: a game is a pair {L|R} where L is the set of Left's options, R the set of Right's options, and every element of L is \"born earlier\" than every element of R. This construction generates not just integers (1 = {0|}, 2 = {1|}, ...) but fractions (½ = {0|1}), infinitesimals (ε = {0|0,ε/2,...}), and infinite ordinals (ω = {0,1,2,...|}).

Conway showed these \"surreal numbers\" have arithmetic, obey the field axioms (with care around infinity), and form the largest possible ordered field. The \"birthday\" of a number is how many steps of recursion it takes to build it. Day 0: {|} = 0. Day 1: {0|} = 1, {|0} = -1. Day 2: {0|1} = ½, {1|} = 2, {-1|} = -2, {-1|0} = -½. And so on to infinity—and beyond.

**The zero game:**

<!-- BUILD: run in interpreter; create and print 0 -->
```scheme
(define zero (game/surreal '() '()))
(game/surreal->string zero)
```
[VISUAL: text `\"{|}\"` representing the zero game (no moves for either player).]

**The games 1 and -1:**

<!-- BUILD: run in interpreter; create 1 and -1 -->
```scheme
(define one (game/surreal (list zero) '()))
(define neg-one (game/surreal '() (list zero)))

(list (game/surreal->string one) (game/surreal->string neg-one))
```
[VISUAL: `(\"{0|}\" \"{|0}\")` — 1 is {0|}, -1 is {|0}.]

**Birthday of a surreal:**

<!-- BUILD: run in interpreter; show birthday -->
```scheme
(list (list 'number 0 'birthday (game/surreal-birthday zero))
      (list 'number 1 'birthday (game/surreal-birthday one))
      (list 'number -1 'birthday (game/surreal-birthday neg-one)))
```
[VISUAL: `((number 0 birthday 0) (number 1 birthday 1) (number -1 birthday 1))` — 0 born day 0, ±1 day 1.]

**Building 2:**

<!-- BUILD: run in interpreter; 2 = {1|} -->
```scheme
(define two (game/surreal (list one) '()))
(list (game/surreal->string two)
      (list 'birthday (game/surreal-birthday two)))
```
[VISUAL: `(\"{1|}\" (birthday 2))` — 2 is {1|}, born day 2.]

**Building ½:**

<!-- BUILD: run in interpreter; ½ = {0|1} -->
```scheme
(define half (game/surreal (list zero) (list one)))
(list (game/surreal->string half)
      (list 'birthday (game/surreal-birthday half)))
```
[VISUAL: `(\"{0|1}\" (birthday 2))` — ½ born day 2, between 0 and 1.]

**Equality test:**

<!-- BUILD: run in interpreter; test if two surreals are equal -->
```scheme
(define another-half (game/surreal (list zero) (list one)))
(game/surreal-eq? half another-half)
```
[VISUAL: `#t` — {0|1} = {0|1}.]

**Ordering surreals:**

<!-- BUILD: run in interpreter; test ≤ -->
```scheme
(list (game/surreal-le? zero one)   ; 0 ≤ 1?
      (game/surreal-le? one half)   ; 1 ≤ ½?
      (game/surreal-le? half one))  ; ½ ≤ 1?
```
[VISUAL: `(#t #f #t)` — 0≤1 true, 1≤½ false, ½≤1 true.]

**Adding surreals:**

<!-- BUILD: run in interpreter; 1 + 1 = 2 -->
```scheme
(define sum (game/surreal-add one one))
(list (game/surreal->string sum)
      (game/surreal-eq? sum two))
```
[VISUAL: `(\"{1|}\" #t)` — 1+1 equals 2.]

**Adding ½ + ½:**

<!-- BUILD: run in interpreter; ½ + ½ = 1 -->
```scheme
(define sum-halves (game/surreal-add half half))
(game/surreal-eq? sum-halves one)
```
[VISUAL: `#t` — ½+½ = 1.]

**Negation:**

<!-- BUILD: run in interpreter; -(½) = -½ -->
```scheme
(define neg-half (game/surreal-neg half))
(game/surreal->string neg-half)
```
[VISUAL: `\"{-1|0}\"` — negation swaps and negates Left/Right sets.]

**Subtraction:**

<!-- BUILD: run in interpreter; 1 - ½ = ½ -->
```scheme
(define diff (game/surreal-sub one half))
(game/surreal-eq? diff half)
```
[VISUAL: `#t` — 1 - ½ = ½.]

**Multiplication—1 × ½:**

<!-- BUILD: run in interpreter; 1 × ½ = ½ -->
```scheme
(define prod (game/surreal-mul one half))
(game/surreal-eq? prod half)
```
[VISUAL: `#t` — surreal multiplication works.]

**Building a negative integer -2:**

<!-- BUILD: run in interpreter; -2 = {|-1} -->
```scheme
(define neg-two (game/surreal '() (list neg-one)))
(list (game/surreal->string neg-two)
      (game/surreal-eq? neg-two (game/surreal-neg two)))
```
[VISUAL: `(\"{|-1}\" #t)` — -2 is {|-1}, equals -(2).]

**Is this a number (not a game with incomparable moves)?**

<!-- BUILD: run in interpreter; test if surreal is a number -->
```scheme
(list (game/surreal-is-number? zero)
      (game/surreal-is-number? half)
      (game/surreal-is-number? (game/surreal (list zero) (list zero)))) ; degenerate
```
[VISUAL: `(#t #t #f)` — {0|0} violates the ordering rule (no Left ≥ Right), so not a number.]

**The simplest number in an interval:**

<!-- BUILD: run in interpreter; simplest number born between 0 and 1 -->
```scheme
(define simplest (game/surreal-simplest zero one))
(game/surreal-eq? simplest half)
```
[VISUAL: `#t` — ½ is the simplest (earliest birthday) number strictly between 0 and 1.]

**Building integers up to 5:**

<!-- BUILD: run in interpreter; construct 0,1,2,3,4,5 -->
```scheme
(define (int->surreal n)
  (if (<= n 0)
      zero
      (game/surreal (list (int->surreal (- n 1))) '())))

(map (lambda (n) (game/surreal->string (int->surreal n))) (comb/range 0 6))
```
[VISUAL: `(\"{|}\" \"{0|}\" \"{1|}\" \"{2|}\" \"{3|}\" \"{4|}\")` — integers as surreals.]

**Converting surreal to real (when possible):**

<!-- BUILD: run in interpreter; to-real -->
```scheme
(map (lambda (s) (game/to-real s))
     (list zero one half two))
```
[VISUAL: `(0.0 1.0 0.5 2.0)` — converts to floating-point where defined.]

**The surreal ¼:**

<!-- BUILD: run in interpreter; ¼ = {0|½} -->
```scheme
(define quarter (game/surreal (list zero) (list half)))
(list (game/surreal->string quarter)
      (game/to-real quarter))
```
[VISUAL: `(\"{0|{0|1}}\" 0.25)` — ¼ is the simplest number between 0 and ½.]

**Building a small surreal tree, showing birthdays:**

<!-- BUILD: run in interpreter; enumerate day-0, day-1, day-2 surreals -->
```scheme
(define day0 (list zero))
(define day1 (list one neg-one))
(define day2 (list two neg-two half (game/surreal (list neg-one) (list zero))))

(map (lambda (x) (list (game/surreal->string x) (game/surreal-birthday x)))
     (append day0 day1 day2))
```
[VISUAL: list showing each surreal with its string form and birthday, illustrating the tree of creation.]

**Star (the first infinitesimal game) as a surreal:**

In surreal notation, *1 (the game {0|0}) is not a number (violates the rule), but it's the prototypical *fuzzy* game (incomparable with 0). We can represent it:

<!-- BUILD: run in interpreter; create *1 = {0|0} -->
```scheme
(define star1 (game/surreal (list zero) (list zero)))
(list (game/surreal->string star1)
      (game/surreal-is-number? star1))
```
[VISUAL: `(\"{0|0}\" #f)` — *1 is a game but not a number.]

**Adding star to a number:**

<!-- BUILD: run in interpreter; 1 + *1 -->
```scheme
(define one-plus-star (game/surreal-add one star1))
(game/surreal->string one-plus-star)
```
[VISUAL: string showing {0|0} added to 1 — complex recursion, result is a game (not simplifying to a number).]

